<div id="#continues-post-newsletter"></div>
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="468" data-total-count="1858">Mr. Brumer became president of the company in 1965, retiring in 1977. He was chief engineer and consultant on highway projects, harbor improvements and tunnel construction throughout the Northeast. When he was chief engineer of the building of the Verrazano-Narrows Bridge, which links Brooklyn and Staten Island, it was at the time of its completion, in 1964, the longest suspension bridge in the world. Its size was surpassed by the Humber Bridge in England in 1981.</p>        <a class="visually-hidden skip-to-text-link" href="#story-continues-2">Continue reading the main story</a>
