    <div class="story-body story-body-2">
        <p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="383" data-total-count="2241" id="story-continues-3">Milton Brumer was born in Philadelphia on Jan. 21, 1902, raised in Brooklyn, and was a longtime resident of Riverdale, in the Bronx. He was recently nominated to the Hall of Fame of the Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, from which he received a mechanical engineering degree and an honorary doctorate of engineering. He also received a master's degree from the University of Alabama.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="106" data-total-count="2347">He was named Engineer of the Year in 1965 by the American Society of Civil Engineers Metropolitan Section.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="187" data-total-count="2534">Mr. Brumer's wife died in 1996. He is survived by two daughters, Barbara Lee Brumer of Boca Raton and Carolyn Faith Graham of Hartsdale, N.Y.; two granddaughters and four great-grandsons.</p>        <a class="visually-hidden skip-to-text-link" href="#whats-next">Continue reading the main story</a>
    </div><!-- close story-body -->
    <div class="supplemental " id="supplemental-2">
    </div><!-- close supplemental -->
</div><!-- close story-body-supplemental -->

    
